1 Oppressed by astonishment, to my guide 2 I turned, like a sparrow that returns 3 always there where one trusts most;
4 and that one, like a mother who helps 5 immediately to the pale and yearning son 6 with her voice, which the earth well arranges,
7 she said: “Do you not know that you are in heaven? 8 and do you not know that heaven is all holy, 9 and that what is done there comes from good zeal?
10 How would the song have transformed you, 11 and I laughing, now you can think it, 12 after that the shout has moved you so much;
13 in which, if you had understood his prayers, 14 already would be known to you the vengeance 15 that you will see before you die.

